{
  "texts": [
    "However, traditional machine learning methods for the processing of point clouds depend on handcrafted features and specifically designed optimization methods.",
    "Point cloud features of static properties are invariant to transformations, therefore, application-oriented optimization methods need to be developed in each case, and generalization cannot be achieved [87].",
    "Therefore, the need for developing enhanced and more efficient methods to process point cloud data is apparent.",
    "DL methods can automatically learn discriminative features, have proven their effectiveness, and therefore have been also adapted to point cloud processing.",
    "Recently, researchers and industrial organizations have employed DL techniques to handle point clouds."
  ]
}